doctype html
head
	meta(charset='utf-8')
	meta(http-equiv='X-UA-Compatible', content='IE=edge')
	meta(name='viewport', content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1')
	title API Basejump: URL Shortener Microservice
	link(rel='stylesheet', media='screen', href='/lib/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css')

body
	.container
		.header 
			a(href="/") back
			h1 API Basejump: URL Shortener Microservice
			h3 
				a(href = "http://www.freecodecamp.com/challenges/basejump-url-shortener-microservice") FreeCodeCamp project
		.panel.panel-default
			.panel-heading
				h3.panel-title User stories:
			ul.list-group
				li.list-group-item   I can pass a URL as a parameter and I will receive a shortened URL in the JSON response.
					br
					strong Example:
					br
					a(href="http://#{host}/api/shorturl/new/http://freecodecamp.com") http://#{host}/api/shorturl/new/http://freecodecamp.com
					br
					strong Response
					code {"original_url":"http://freecodecamp.com","short_url":"http://#{host}/api/shorturl/2"}
				li.list-group-item  If I pass an invalid URL that doesn't follow the valid http://www.example.com format, the JSON response will contain an error instead.
					br
					strong Example:
					br
					a(href="http://#{host}/api/shorturl/new/in.valid.url") http://#{host}/api/shorturl/new/in.valid.url
					br
					strong Response
					code {"error":"URL invalid"}
				li.list-group-item  When I visit that shortened URL, it will redirect me to my original link.
					br
					strong Example:
					br
					a(href="http://#{host}/api/shorturl/2") http://#{host}/api/shorturl/2
			.panel-footer
				a(href="https://github.com/golle404/Basejump-URL-Shortener-Microservice") source

